  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Global Hub Support Centre</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide easy access to services MapAction has established a triage, prioritisation and management system, The Covid-19 Hub, within our Global Help Centre. This will enable efficient assessment of the likely impact, urgency and technical challenge of each task request. We will prioritise the requests likely to have the greatest impact on the most vulnerable populations. In particular these will be: a) Global analysis and coordination through established structures, b) Country level scale up of response, c) Support to chronic emergencies secondarily impacted by the Covid-19 storm (e.g. Current MapAction support to Camp Coordination Cluster Management in NW Syria) d) Thematic areas such as accountability. 
We have already started promoting the Covid-19 Service to priority countries and responding organisations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Informing effective humanitarian planning and response through the 
provision of geospatial and data products/services to key coordination and response organisations from global through to local levels for Covid-19 measures and secondary impacts of Covid-19</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our support is via a wide range of partner organisations and we will reach affected people through these partners. Some are large scale INGO/NGOSs and UN agencies delivering direct services. Others are H2H partners including CartONG, HOT, ACAPS, Ground Truth Solutions, Translators without Borders involved in communicating with affected communities and promoting accountability.</narrative>
  </description>
